genresAdvancedInfo.name: junior songfestival
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Junior Songfestival is a Dutch television program and competition for young singers aged between 10 and 15 years old. The show features aspiring artists performing original songs in front of a live audience and a panel of judges, and the winner is chosen through a combination of jury and public voting. Junior Songfestival provides a unique opportunity for young talents to develop their skills, gain exposure, and potentially launch a career in the music industry.
